The paper discusses the development of a human-centered approach to the design and implementation of software robots, which involves the use of AI methods and tools, including machine learning. This makes it likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category, as well as Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of tailored high-level RPA Domain Specific Languages (DSLs) to adjust the functioning of the robots, which suggests a focus on Software Engineering (cs.SE) as well. Finally, the paper also mentions the use of interactive and collaborative ML in the cloud, which could indicate a focus on Machine Learning (cs.LG) as well.
